Class BipartiteGraph<L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • homework2.BipartiteGraph<L>

  • public class BipartiteGraph<L>
extends java.lang.Object
    A BipartiteGraph is an abstraction of a graph that has two groups of nodes: black nodes and white nodes. In a bipartite graph there can only be edges from white nodes to black nodes and vice versa (i.e. no edges between nodes that are of the same color). Thus, a typical BipartiteGraph has the properties {whiteNodes, blackNodes}.
